AB  - The objective of this paper is to study the stationarity of beta-coefficients of common stocks through time. Special attention is paid to the influence of errors in the estimated betas on various measures of stationarity. The results indicate that even for small porfolios the true betas (as opposed to estimated betas) are reasonably stable.
