AB  - Eps (earning per share) is widely used as a financial measure of performance, but it can be misleading in takeovers and mergers. Conditions are examined under which the eps of a combined enterprise is greater than that of each of the constituent companies prior to the bid, and the relative gains to the bidder (in terms of earning) are stated.
